column3: Built NEW.  Installed NEW Iridium SIM Card.
Successfully tested all MET sensor inputs, RF modem, IM data, and GPS.
Tried to run bench current drain test, but it seems like the RF modem is NOT turning OFF.  Current seems about 20mA higher than other systems.
Did some bench testing.  Current drain seemed higher when first powered up, around 66mA, but then RF modem did turn off and current drain seemed reasonable.
Installed SS metal circuit board standoffs on bottom stack.
Ran Bench current drain test for 4.5 days with version 2.01, 170530 firmware, RF modem turned off okay, 15.71mA Average.
Tested internal Iridium antenna by doing an XMIT outside, which successfully registered and sent dummy files.
